cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper proposes an enhanced LSTM architecture for sentence semantic modeling using typed dependencies. The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as semantic relatedness scoring and sentiment analysis. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a Tree-LSTM model, which can be related to cs.LG (Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses NLP tasks that involve text data, which can also be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
